// SOURCE: Source Files/Intergrations/Fusion Intergrations 3/Technical Sheet.txt
// NOTE: Integrated into the Fusion FSN tree for migration traceability.
// CONTENT:
// Technical Sheet: Fusion IonArchitectureIon is a Driver. It does not implement a parser itself; it wraps existing robust frontends (rustc, clang) but controls their code generation pipeline.Frontend Phase: Invokes rustc --emit=llvm-bc or clang -emit-llvm.Optimization Phase: Invokes opt (LLVM Optimizer) with hardware-specific passes.Backend Phase: Invokes llc (LLVM Static Compiler) to generate machine code.Link Phase: Invokes lld (LLVM Linker).Hardware DetectionIon uses the raw_cpuid crate to detect features:x86_64: SSE4.2, AVX, AVX2, AVX-512F, FMA3, BMI1/2.AArch64: NEON, SVE, LSE.Output FormatsExecutable: Standard ELF/Mach-O/PE.Fusion Runtime Image (.fri): A containerized format for Supernova.WASM: wasm32-wasi or wasm32-unknown-unknown.
